"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Cutting up the furrows in soil and turning it up before work can be done on the land.</p>\n<h2>Ploughing as a way of life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:19-1Kgs19:21\">1KI 19:19–19:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:7\">LUK 17:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:12\">1SA 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:19-1Sam13:21\">1SA 13:19–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:14\">JOB 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:4\">PRO 20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:24\">ISA 28:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:9\">EZK 36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:13\">AMO 9:13</a></p>\n<h2>Rules concerning ploughing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10-Exod23:11\">EXO 23:10–23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:10\">DEU 22:10</a></p>\n<h2>Ploughing used figuratively</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:8\">JOB 4:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:62\">LUK 9:62</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:18\">JDG 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps129:3\">PSA 129:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:7\">PSA 141:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:4\">ISA 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:3\">JER 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:11-Hos10:12\">HOS 10:11–10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:12\">AMO 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:10\">1CO 9:10</a></p>",
